// Adversarial: BumpWhiffOccurred fires a DamageBoost(2.5) via Once (consumed on first whiff)
// and a Shockwave on every whiff. These are installed as two separate Stamps — Sequence
// cannot hold a Once (Tree::Sequence takes Terminals only). Dense layout maximises
// bolt-breaker contact events, and chaos 0.5 produces a natural mix of successful bumps
// and mistimed whiffs.
// The adversarial risk: if the BumpWhiffOccurred bridge evaluates the When/Once node more
// than once per whiff event (e.g., due to double-read of BumpWhiffed), DamageBoost stacks
// silently and the Shockwave spawns duplicate rings that are never cleaned up.
// If BumpWhiffOccurred fires even when no bump input was registered, the Once is consumed
// prematurely and the effect is lost. NoEntityLeaks detects leaked Shockwave ring
// entities that fail to expand and despawn. BoltSpeedAccurate catches indirect
// speed corruption from a runaway DamageBoost multiplier. NoNaN guards against
// uninitialized velocity in spawned Shockwave entities. 5000 frames at moderate
// chaos ensures many whiff events without exhausting the node prematurely.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2311,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(ActiveBolts, Once(BumpWhiffOccurred, Fire(DamageBoost((multiplier: 2.5))))),
        Stamp(ActiveBolts, When(BumpWhiffOccurred, Fire(Shockwave((base_range: 50.0, range_per_level: 0.0, stacks: 1, speed: 200.0))))),
    ],
)
